ess has asked to be released? -- t25. It has been claimed that the Chinese have tried prisoners in Tibet at mass rallies, after which they were immediately killed. Is it true? -- t26. Some people have accused China of carrying out “racial segregation” and “racial discrimination” in Tibet. What is the reality? -- t27. Some people have said that Tibetans cannot act freely in Tibet, and that Tibetan cadres and children aged under 18 cannot travel abroad. Is this true? -- t28. The Dalai Lama and others say that Tibetan children have been deprived of the right to education and that Tibet has become an area of illiteracy. Is this true? -- t29. It is reported that there are serious problems of unemployment and child labor among the Tibetans. Is that true? -- t30. People at the side of the Dalai Lama also said that the hospitals in Tibet only serve the Han people. Is that true? -- t31. How long is the average life span of Tibetans living in Tibet? How is it compared with what it was before the peaceful liberation of Tibet? -- t32. Some people have claimed that China practised forced sterilization and the killing of infants in Tibet. Is this true? -- tPart Three. Policies toward the Dalai Lama -- tIntroduction -- t33. What policy has the central government adopted toward the Dalai Lama? -- t34. If the Dalai Lama returns, can he settle in Tibet? -- t35. What is the attitude of the Chinese government toward the Dalai Lama’s visit to other countries? -- t36. What is the basic divergence of views between the Dalai Lama and the Chinese government and people? -- t37. What is the Chinese government’s attitude toward the “fivepoint proposal” put forward by the Dalai Lama in the United States during September 1987? -- t38. How does the Chinese government view the Dalai Lama’s “New proposal” on Tibet he put forward in Strasbourg, France, in June 1988? -- t39. How does the Chinese government value the idea of a “greater Tibetan autonomous region” suggested by some people around the Dalai Lama? -- t40. Why doesn’t China agree to apply the “one country, two systems” concept to Tibet? -- t41. Will the Chinese government permit the Tibetans who fled abroad with the Dalai Lama and have acquired foreign citizenships to return? If so, what formalities should they go through before their homecoming visit? -- t42. What relations does the self-exiled Dalai Lama maintain with the Bainqen Lama? -- tPart Four. Population -- tIntroduction -- t43. Has there been a decrease in the number of Tibetans since the peaceful liberation of Tibet in 1951? -- t44. Dalai and his followers claim that 7.5 million Han have been emigrated to Tibet, and that Tibetans have become a minority nationality in the region. Is that true? -- t45. What is the Tibetan population? How is it distributed? -- t46. How many minority nationalities are there in China? -- t47. How many minority ethnic groups are there in Tibet? -- tPart Five. Religious Belief -- tIntroduction -- t48. What policies has the Chinese government adopted toward religious belief in Tibet? -- t49. Some people claim that the Chinese Communist Party has eliminated religion in Tibet. Is this true? -- t50. Did the Chinese government appropriate money for renovating monasteries in Tibet in order to attract more foreign tourists? -- t51. Are Tibetans free to take part in religious activities? -- t52. How are Tibet’s monasteries administered? -- t53. Are there any professional schools for training religious workers in Tibet? -- t54. Please give a brief account of the lamasery life. Do lamas suffer many privations? -- t55. Which monasteries are famous in Tibet? And what is the situation they are in now? -- t56. When did Tibetan Buddhism come into being? How many sects does it have? -- t57. It has been reported that China will set up a “Tibetan Buddhism Guidance Committee.” What will be its tasks? -- tPart Six. Right to autonomy -- tIntroduction -- t58. What policies has the Chinese government adopted in regard to minority nationalities? -- t59. When was the Tibet Autonomous Region founded? How many autonomous regions are there in China? -- t60. As one of the autonomous regions, what rights does Tibet have? -- t61. How many decrees on self-government have been formulated by the Tibet Autonomous Region? -- t62. What is the proportion of Tibetans to Han in the Tibet Autonomous Region’s civil service? -- t63. Who were the heads of all previous governments of the Tibet Autonomous Region? Were they all Tibetans? -- t64. Who have served as the standing committee chairmen of the Tibet Autonomous Regional People’s Congress? What nationality were they? -- t65. How many counties and cities does the Tibet Autonomous Region have under its jurisdiction? What are the nationalities of the county magistrates and mayors? -- t66. Are there any other Tibet autonomous areas in China apart from the Tibet Autonomous Region? -- t67. Why are none of the first secretaries of the Tibet Autonomous Regional Committee of the Chinese Communist Party Tibetans? -- tPart Seven. Culture and education -- tIntroduction -- t68. 00tWhat is the policy adopted by China regarding traditional Tibetan culture? -- t69. Some foreign newspapers have claimed that China has paid no attention to Tibet’s history and culture. What are the facts? -- t70. What is the Chinese government’s attitude toward traditional Tibetan literature and art? -- t71. What work has been done to protect cultural relics and historical sites in Tibet? -- t72. What is the situation of Tibetan studies in China? -- t73. What does the China Tibetan Studies Center do? Who runs it? -- t74. It is said that traditional Tibetan medical science is very special. What has China done to develop it? -- t75. How about the use of the Tibetan language? -- tPart Eight. Economic development -- tIntroduction -- tHistorical Comparisons -- tThe Legacy of State Intervention in the Tibetan Areas over the Past Fifty Years